OL,6,FIn a witness statement, Grealish told
OL,7,Fpolice he could not hear what the
OL,8,Fdefendant was shouting due to the
OL,9,Fcrowd noise, so he walked towards him
OL,10,Fand tried to engage in conversation
OL,11,Fand leaned in to speak to the
OL,12,Fdefendant.
OL,14,FHe was still unable to hear, so he
OL,15,Fmoved to walk away when he was slapped.
OL,17,FAfter his arrest, Holt told police he
OL,18,Fhad been drinking before the game "in
OL,19,Ftown" and went to the match with his
OL,20,Ffather.
